        "title": "How to mock constructow without interference in legacy code",
        "body": "<p>How to mock constructor without interference in legacy code using only Mockito (not PowerMockito). I made a research and I found some solutions but all of them base on interference on legacy code (creating factory, fake Method etc). Thanks for any responses. Here snippet of code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    NyxBasicService&lt;CreateAccountModel&gt; accountService = new NyxBasicService&lt;CreateAccountModel&gt;(\n        CreateAccountModel.class, null, sessionService);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>To this time I used PowerMockito sth like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>whenNew(NyxCommunicator.class).withAnyArguments().thenReturn(nyxCommunicator);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The thing is that I have to remove PowerMockito from my project and use only Mockito. Another thing is that inside constructor there is realy handsome amount of logic.<\/p>\n",
